<br>
I've picked 4 profiles, showing what might be interesting to people viewing here.<br>
<br>
Assumptions:<br>
Earring: 7.5% mana reduction on all DD (rain / direct / bolt).<br>
Ring: 10% casting time reduction on all spells.<br>
Bracer: 10% increase in damage on direct and bolt spells.<br>
<br>
SCM1: 2.5% savings on all spells<br>
SCM2: 7.5%<br>
SCM3: 15%<br>
<br>
SCF1: 0.7% increase in damage on all spells<br>
SCF2: 2.7%<br>
SCF3: 7%<br>
SCF4: 9% (FoM1)<br>
SCF5: 12% (FoM2)<br>
SCF6: 14% (FoM3)<br>
<br>
Primary speciailization: 10% off casting cost from that school<br>
Other specialization: 2.5% off casting cost from that school<br>
<br>
Damage mitigation is used to account for factors that reduce  damage output -- ie increased resists, low-health rain immunity, bolt blockage.  I've made my best guess at what these should be.  I'm guessing:<br>
<br>
5% of bolts are blocked<br>
20% extra resists on rain  <br>
<br>
Wizards are reporting 20% resist on lure-style rains (<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessage?topicID=24601.topic" target="top">Graffe's Rain Study</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->), and I personally simply don't believe that rains and DD's are resisted similarly.<br>
<br>
The best use for these charts, IMO, are as a comparison of dpm side by side for selection of which nuke to use, based on your school of specialization.  Notice how much difference focus items alone make... its hard to argue that we haven't been seriously upgraded since the release of SoL.<br>
<br>
*edit -- note, the omission of Manastorm was not intentional, I simply forgot it. I doubt it has much to add to the overall picture. -- edit*<br>
<br>
